<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-06-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-06-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="1074" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1074">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 831.415 A/11.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">American
                                Minister</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-06-12"><hi rend="italic">June 12,
                                1911</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The President has decided to send a special ambassador, accompanied by a
                            secretary and military and naval attaches, to the centenary of
                            Venezuelan independence. Mr. Thomas C. Dawson is named special
                            ambassador and Capt. Marsh, United States Navy, commanding the U. S. S.
                                <hi rend="italic">North Carolina</hi>, will be naval attaché to the
                            special mission. The above named vessel will carry the mission to La
                            Guaira, Venezuela. The names of the secretary and military attaché to
                            the mission will be sent later.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>